snippet.textDisplay: I've owned two PT's, bought one new in 2004, the only year the PT had a true purple as an option. The second in 2015 was the GT model, and it was fast. My OBDII reader was telling me the car was at 14psi on the boost so I think it may have been upgraded to stage one at some point. You can easily get over 300-400hp out those engines. What I like about the car aside from it's appearance, was the way you sat in it. You sat upright like in a truck, and I like the fold down seats where you could eat lunch or place you laptop. I like everything about the car, and think it will have a resurgence some day which imo, makes the PT a car to collect. If I had the money, i'd be snatching these up for a future junk/parts yard.

You're right, No one asked for this. These cars are part time cruisers because the rest of the time they were sitting on the side of a road after bursting into flames or in some poor idiots garage which is the best place for them because the kind of people who deliberately buy these things are the exact people that shouldn't have a drivers license.
